Ran into an interesting issue today while adding supabase authentication to our bolt.new + Expo app:
‚ùå iOS Bundling failed
The package at "node_modules/ws/lib/stream.js" attempted to import the Node standard library module "stream". It failed because the native React runtime does not include the Node standard library.


Turns out the issue is caused by ws, a dependency of supabase-js, trying to use a Node-specific module ‚Äî which obviously doesn‚Äôt play nice with the Expo runtime.
‚úÖ Fix
https://github.com/supabase/supabase-js/issues/1400
You need to add a custom metro.config.js file to shim Node core modules:
// metro.config.js
const { getDefaultConfig } = require("expo/metro-config");

const config = getDefaultConfig(__dirname);

// Add this for Node core module fallbacks
config.resolver.nodeModulesPaths = ["node_modules"];
config.resolver.extraNodeModules = {
  stream: require.resolve("readable-stream"),
};

module.exports = config;

Hope this saves someone else the headache! If you‚Äôre integrating Supabase into a new Expo app, especially with bolt.new, make sure you‚Äôve got this tweak in place.
